Our People

No celebrity fund managers or hard sell. Just 350 employees dedicated to our independent-minded culture, working hard to put clients first. Allow us to introduce a few of them.



 






Management Team



Our Management Team have an outstanding level of investment experience. With professional backgrounds ranging from law to fund management to the IT business, they have one goal in common – to make investing accessible.









Will Gray
Director



President and Chief Investment Officer, Orbis Investment Management Ltd.
Director, Orbis Funds



Will graduated from the University of Cape Town as a Bachelor of Commerce, holds a Master of Business Administration from Harvard University, and is a CFA Institute charterholder.
Upon completing his...
View full bio



Will graduated from the University of Cape Town as a Bachelor of Commerce, holds a Master of Business Administration from Harvard University, and is a CFA Institute charterholder.
Upon completing his MBA he joined Orbis Investment Management Limited in 1993 to analyse North American securities. He has three years’ previous experience conducting investment research into global equities, stock markets and currencies for Orbis Investment Advisory Limited and for Orbis Investment Management Limited’s predecessor in Hong Kong.









Alec Cutler
Director



Co-Manager & Director, Orbis Investment Management Ltd.
Director, Orbis Investment Management (BVI) Ltd.



Alec holds a Bachelor of Science (Honours) in Naval Architecture from the United States Naval Academy, a Master of Business Administration from The Wharton School, University of Pennsylvania, and is a...
View full bio



Alec holds a Bachelor of Science (Honours) in Naval Architecture from the United States Naval Academy, a Master of Business Administration from The Wharton School, University of Pennsylvania, and is a CFA Institute charterholder. 
Prior to joining Orbis in 2004 he was at Brandywine Asset Management Ltd, where he managed the Relative Value product, co-managed the Large Cap Value area and co-managed the firm as a member of the Executive Committee.









James Dorr
Director



General Counsel & Secretary, Orbis Funds & Orbis Investment Management Ltd.
Director, Orbis Access UK Ltd. 



James graduated from Queen's University with a Bachelor of Science (Honours) and a Bachelor of Laws. He also received a Master of Laws from the University of Cambridge and is a Barrister and Solicitor....
View full bio



James graduated from Queen's University with a Bachelor of Science (Honours) and a Bachelor of Laws. He also received a Master of Laws from the University of Cambridge and is a Barrister and Solicitor. Prior to joining Orbis in 1998 he practised corporate securities law for nine years as a partner in the law firm Davies, Ward & Beck in Toronto, Canada.









Adam Karr
Director



Managing Director, Orbis Investment Management (US) LLC
Director, Orbis Investment Management Ltd. 



Adam holds a Bachelor of Arts in Economics from Northwestern University and a Master of Business Administration from Harvard University.  
Before joining Orbis in 2002, Adam spent five years as a...
View full bio



Adam holds a Bachelor of Arts in Economics from Northwestern University and a Master of Business Administration from Harvard University.  
Before joining Orbis in 2002, Adam spent five years as a partner at Palladium Equity Partners, a private equity firm in New York City, where he was responsible for investing in private companies. He also spent two years as a financial analyst with Donaldson, Lufkin & Jenrette Securities Corp in New York City, where he participated in a broad range of investment banking and principal investment activities.









Dan Brocklebank
Director



Director at Orbis Access UK Limited 
Equity Analyst at Orbis Investments



Dan holds a Master of Arts (Honours) in Politics, Philosophy and Economics from Brasenose College, University of Oxford. After that, he qualified as a Chartered Accountant and Chartered Financial Analyst....
View full bio



Dan holds a Master of Arts (Honours) in Politics, Philosophy and Economics from Brasenose College, University of Oxford. After that, he qualified as a Chartered Accountant and Chartered Financial Analyst. 
Dan joined Orbis in 2002 and is responsible for the UK-based team of global sector investment analysts.









